data.prompt:
Extract comprehensive customer insights from reviews about Smart Wi-Fi Enabled Dimmer Switches.
The output format is JSON in English:
{
"phy": {
"<PHYSICAL>": {
"<PID>@<DETAIL>": {
"<SENT>": [ID, …]
}
}
},
"perf": {
"<PERF>": {
"<perf_id>@<DETAIL>": {
"<SENT>": {<PERF_REASON>: [ID, …]}
}
}
},
"use": {
"<USE>": {
"<SENT>": {<USE_REASON>: [ID, …]}
}
}
}

Definitions:
- <PID>: Unique ID for physical aspect ("phy"), starting from A. After Z, continue with AA, AB, and so on.
- <PHYSICAL>: Components or inherent physical properties of the Smart Wi-Fi Enabled Dimmer Switches without external interaction (e.g. dimensions, appearance, material type...)
- <DETAIL>: A self-contained detail summarized from the reviews.
- <SENT>: Sentiment polarity of the current <DETAIL> (- for negative, + for positive).
- ID: All review IDs mentioning the <DETAIL>
- <perf_id>: Unique ID for performance or functions ("perf"), starting from a. After z, continue with aa, ab, and so on.
- <PERF>: The Smart Wi-Fi Enabled Dimmer Switches' performance (e.g. flexibility, durability, ...) or behaviors under various conditions (e.g. temperature, force, chemicals...) without reference to any specific use case
- <PERF_REASON>: <PID> of the <PHYSICAL> explicitly mentioned as the cause of the <PERF>. Include all mentioned <PID>s. If no reason is mentioned, use "?". <PERF_REASON> and <PERF> should have the same sentiment polarity in the review where they are mentioned together (i.e. the same review ID are included at both locations)
- <USE>: The specific application, applicable object, method, tool, or environment for the product.
- <USE_REASON>: <perf_id> or <PID> causing the <USE>'s sentiment. Include all mentioned reasons, or "?" if none can be inferred. <USE_REASON> and <USE> should have the same sentiment polarity in the review where they are mentioned together.

CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS:
- <PHYSICAL>/<PERF> and <DETAIL> MUST NOT include:
  * Generic statements without details (e.g., "good", "bad quality")
  * Issues unrelated to the product itself (e.g., "fast shipping", "delivery time")
- If a review mentions any physical aspect, related performance, or use together, extract them as separate entries under "phy," "perf," and "use," with no overlap.
- Make sure each <DETAIL> is under the most relevant <PHYSICAL> or <PERF> in the context of Smart Wi-Fi Enabled Dimmer Switches
- Preserve negations

Key Instructions:
- Break down reviews with multiple aspects, performances, or uses into individual entries.
- Escape special characters with backslash that could cause JSON syntax errors.
- Include only explicitly mentioned reasons, and use "?" where no reason is mentioned.

Final Checklist:
- Go through all reviews and ensure that no aspect, performance, use, or reason is omitted, even if only mentioned once.
- Review all entries to ensure proper separation between aspects, performances, and uses.

Print the JSON result only.
Input format:
<ID>#<review>

[[INPUT]]
0#Doesn't dim far enough. Quality switch, easy to add to HomeKit, I wish they dimmed further. The 2-way switches dim the lights significantly more, at the lowest setting it's too bright for me.
1#Dead. Lights can’t be turned off!!! First one I installed has now locked in the on position. Unresponsive to WiFi AND the physical switch. Completely defective. Out of return window for Amazon.
2#Started great but failed after a couple of months. Connected well to the phone and Siri but it flickers all the time. I installed it at 4 different locations and the flickering is so annoying. I like their other products tbh but this light switch was a disappointment. The problem could be something else but we have other dimmable light switches in the house and those are always fine. This was a waste of money.
3#Flawed design. They are great if they work. When (and not if) they crash - a weird concept for a light switch, but essentially disconnect from the WiFi - the physical switch buttons will stop working as well! One has to switch the circuit breaker from the panel off and on to “restart” the switch.
4#Used Switches in a Sealed Box! I bought a bunch of these switches (like 30) a little over a month ago. I recognize that’s a while, but I bought them for a new house and am just getting moved in. While I’ve installed about 20 and they’ve gone well so far, when I opened my last “4 pack” I was surprised to find that the switches were used! Granted, the box was completely sealed. 2 of the switches were some old style switch and all had seemingly been installed previously (look at the photos of the wire ends). Also, one of the old style had a yellow post-it note that says “bad” on it! How does this happen?!?! Amazon is refunding, but it still screws up my install process (and they couldn’t care less), plus I have to go through a reorder process to re-buy them at a now increased price! They say they’ll adjust the price for me if I contract them again after I receive the new product. What a pain… the process just seems to get worse and worse with Amazon. On the switches, I’d say they’re easy to install and setup and they integrate seamlessly with HomeKit. I have no complaints at all about the new/working products and would recommend them, but I might not recommend buying the 4 packs and possibly buy them from someone other than Amazon (maybe Meross directly). My rating: 5 stars for the working products, -5 stars for the 4 pack and 2 stars for Amazon support.
5#Works great! Easy install. Connects easily to Apple HomeKit. So much better than my old smart switches.
6#great product. easy to install
7#Reliable, responsive, and easy to set up. Just as easy to install as any other light switch, and connecting them to a smart home is straight forward. I’ve had them for a while now and had no issues with connectivity.

